records.addlTxt:
Defendant Leenai Lor in court with attorney Reyna Ivonne Morales.  Ronald Dague appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: sm 
Sentencing proceeded. Statements made by State and Defense.  State advised the Court they have complied with the Victims' Rights Law.

 The Court sentenced defendant to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Corrections, with credit for 4 days time served.  Court STAYED sentence and placed the defendant on PROBATION for a period of  1 YEAR with the following conditions:

-Restitution set at $ 0 
-Defendant to pay Court costs and all applicable surcharges and assessments during term of probation; nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay the related surcharge during term of probation; nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment
-No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause
-Cooperate with any correctional programs recommended
-Follow all rules of probation
-Pay all supervision fees; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment 
-Cooperate with agent
-Obtain/maintain full-time employment 
-Obtain GED or HSED
-No contact with: Eh S; Hehbul W; 1925 N 35th Street, Milwaukee, WI
-AODA assessment and any recommended treatment
-Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzers
-No alcohol or illegal drugs
- No weapons or firearms
-Defendant to perform 50 hours of community service 

Defendant taken into custody on an Outstanding Warrant in another county.

Defendant Leenai Lor in court with attorney Reyna Ivonne Morales.  Ronald Dague appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Pursuant to plea negotiations, and on motion of the State, Court ordered charge amended to Criminal Trespass pursuant to Wisc. Stats. sec. 943.14, a Class A Misdemeanor.   Defendant changes plea to GUILTY to the amended charge.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the amended information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.   Court ordered defendant provide a DNA sample.  Payment of the surcharge will be addressed on day of sentencing.

Defendant Leenai Lor in court with attorney Reyna Ivonne Morales.  Ronald Dague appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Original Amended Information received and filed.  Defense acknowledges receipt of the Amended Information, waives reading and enters a plea of not guilty on behalf of his client.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for June 10, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Leenai Lor in court with attorney Reyna Ivonne Morales.  Ronald Dague appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Parties request this matter be scheduled for Jury Trial and Final Pretrial.  Final pre-trial scheduled for May 25, 2016 at 01:30 pm.  Jury trial scheduled for May 31, 2016 at 10:00 am.

Defendant Leenai Lor in court with attorney Francisco Araiza for   Scheduling conference held between counsel.  Parties engaged in settlement negotiations.  Defense requests date for possible resolution of this matter.  Matter scheduled for a "soft" plea hearing.  Plea hearing scheduled for March 17, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Leenai Lor in court with attorney Reyna Ivonne Morales.  James Griffin for Ronald Dague appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   
Defendant waived Preliminary Hearing.  Preliminary Hearing Questionnaire and Waiver received and filed. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.   Defendant is advised that this case is assigned to Judge Cimpl Branch 19.   Original Information filed.  Copy given to defense counsel who waived reading.  Defendant pled not guilty. Court ordered case adjourned for Scheduling Conference in Branch 19.  Scheduling conference scheduled for February 9, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Commissioner advised DNA sample has been obtained from the Defendant.  Court advised Defendant he may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if he meets the conditions under Wisconsin Statutes Section 165.77(4).

Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with Eh S., Hehbul W. and 1925 N. 25th Street, Milwaukee, WI.
Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Leenai Lor in court with attorney Reyna Ivonne Morales.  Kelly O'Neill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: KAR.
Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Cimpl, Branch 19.  Defendant given a copy of complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT DOES QUALIFY FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Case is adjourned for preliminary hearing in Branch PE.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for January 22, 2016 at 08:30 am.
Defendant is Out-of-Custody. Court appearance in Out-Of-Custody Court, Room 221 Safety Building on 1-5-16 @ 1:30pm
